and then served them
at a dinner party

00:12:00,289 --> 00:12:02,825
for $250 plate.

00:12:02,825 --> 00:12:04,260
Lowballed.

00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:05,728
(laughs)

00:12:05,728 --> 00:12:07,363
Look at that.

00:12:07,363 --> 00:12:09,332
Dark pigmentation
on the chicharone.

00:12:09,332 --> 00:12:11,200
Maybe I can reconstitute it.

00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,935
♪ ♪

00:12:29,452 --> 00:12:31,821
(beeping)

00:12:31,821 --> 00:12:33,289
That's a tattoo.

00:12:33,289 --> 00:12:34,757
Where have I
seen that before?

00:12:37,326 --> 00:12:39,629
I would call you chef,

00:12:39,629 --> 00:12:41,964
but that would demean
the entire profession.

00:12:41,964 --> 00:12:43,766
PHILLIPS:
That's the tattoo,

00:12:43,766 --> 00:12:45,201
but that's not Graham Deveraux.

00:12:45,201 --> 00:12:46,536
No, that's Derek Barlow.

00:12:46,536 --> 00:12:47,970
Who was just eliminated
from the show?

00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:50,173
And now eliminated for good.

00:12:54,777 --> 00:12:56,446
So, Derek Barlow
is not our killer.

00:12:56,446 --> 00:12:58,681
He's our victim.
DNA just confirmed it.

00:12:58,681 --> 00:13:00,349
Okay, where's Deveraux?

00:13:00,349 --> 00:13:01,784
Still unaccounted for.

00:13:01,784 --> 00:13:03,653
Oh. A lot of
killers miss work

00:13:03,653 --> 00:13:05,488
the day after
they commit murder.

00:13:05,488 --> 00:13:08,658
Anyway, we know that
Deveraux had an altercation

00:13:08,658 --> 00:13:10,259
with Barlow yesterday.

00:13:10,259 --> 00:13:11,928
Maybe we have
the right players,

00:13:11,928 --> 00:13:14,697
just in the wrong roles.

00:13:14,697 --> 00:13:16,866
You ask me,
they're both scumbags.

00:13:16,866 --> 00:13:18,734
Especially Derek.

00:13:18,734 --> 00:13:20,803
I know, as a producer,
I'm supposed to be impartial,

00:13:20,803 --> 00:13:22,438
but that guy was a piece
of work.

00:13:22,438 --> 00:13:24,740
He did not appear
that way on the show.

00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,242
He was a great chef,

00:13:26,242 --> 00:13:28,511
and I wanted the audience
to root for him,

00:13:28,511 --> 00:13:30,880
so I cut out a lot of the stuff
where he was being an ass.

00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:33,349
I can show you
the raw footage.

00:13:33,349 --> 00:13:34,917
Sure.

00:13:38,921 --> 00:13:41,791
(sizzling)

00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:42,925
(plate crashes)

00:13:42,925 --> 00:13:44,494
What the hell?!

00:13:44,494 --> 00:13:46,796
Why don't you pick up
your mess, sweetheart?

00:13:46,796 --> 00:13:47,930
You're such an ass!

00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:49,499
(laughs)
(sighs)

00:13:49,499 --> 00:13:50,633
DEREK:
Mmm!

00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:51,901
That is exactly how

00:13:51,901 --> 00:13:54,270
I like seeing my ladies
in the kitchen--

00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:55,638
on their hands and knees.

00:13:55,638 --> 00:13:57,206
Ugh.

00:13:57,206 --> 00:13:58,574
That's just the tip
of the iceberg.

00:13:58,574 --> 00:14:00,576
He tried to sabotage
all the contestants.

00:14:00,576 --> 00:14:02,345
Now this seems personal.

00:14:02,345 --> 00:14:05,815
I mean, who would have hated him
enough to want to cook him?

00:14:05,815 --> 00:14:09,252
To be honest, I wouldn't
put it past any of them.

00:14:09,252 --> 00:14:10,753
Derek tried to sabotage me.

00:14:10,753 --> 00:14:11,888
Well, screw him.

00:14:11,888 --> 00:14:13,523
(laughing)

00:14:13,523 --> 00:14:15,925
I always thought
his cooking was overrated.

00:14:15,925 --> 00:14:18,494
He's gone,
and I'm in the final four.

00:14:18,494 --> 00:14:19,795
With Derek out of the way,

00:14:19,795 --> 00:14:21,898
I really think
I can win this thing.

00:14:21,898 --> 00:14:24,834
BRODY:
Greg and I were able to recover
<i>most</i> of Derek Barlow.

00:14:24,834 --> 00:14:27,937
ROBBINS:
At least the parts that didn't
make it to the dinner table.

00:14:27,937 --> 00:14:29,505
You know, I read somewhere

00:14:29,505 --> 00:14:31,507
that the Yanomamo
tribe in the Amazon

00:14:31,507 --> 00:14:33,342
consume pieces
of their deceased loved ones

00:14:33,342 --> 00:14:34,677
as an act of mourning.

00:14:34,677 --> 00:14:37,213
A way of keeping them alive
within them.

00:14:37,213 --> 00:14:39,916
Well, I don't think that was
the case with Mr. Barlow here.

00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,817
Finlay said everyone hated him.

00:14:41,817 --> 00:14:43,953
Yes, but at least
the killer was kind enough

00:14:43,953 --> 00:14:46,789
to kill Mr. Barlow before
they dismembered and cooked him.

00:14:46,789 --> 00:14:50,259
Look at the margins near
the disarticulations.

00:14:50,259 --> 00:14:51,827
Skin is blanched.

00:14:51,827 --> 00:14:53,296
Orange in color.

00:14:53,296 --> 00:14:55,698
Blood wasn't circulating.

00:14:55,698 --> 00:14:57,700
May I?

00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,569
Go ahead.

00:14:59,569 --> 00:15:01,437
Looks like he's
had a head injury.

00:15:01,437 --> 00:15:04,540
Found that examining
underneath his hairline.

00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:07,410
Based on the bruising,
at least 48 hours old.

00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:08,811
It's unrelated to his death.

00:15:08,811 --> 00:15:10,646
So, what's C.O.D.?

00:15:10,646 --> 00:15:12,815
Exsanguination due to multiple
sharp force injuries.

00:15:12,815 --> 00:15:16,485
Based on the width
and depth of the wounds,

00:15:16,485 --> 00:15:19,188
I'd say the killer used
a single-edged knife

00:15:19,188 --> 00:15:22,291
with approximately
a seven-inch blade.

00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:25,595
Do you think the killer used
the same knife to dismember him?

00:15:25,595 --> 00:15:26,729
No, I don't believe so.

00:15:26,729 --> 00:15:28,397
Look at the radius
and ulna here--

00:15:28,397 --> 00:15:29,799
not a mark on them.

00:15:29,799 --> 00:15:31,567
The flesh was removed
with great skill

00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:33,869
and with the proper knife.

00:15:33,869 --> 00:15:35,671
A boning knife.

00:15:35,671 --> 00:15:38,374
Yeah, something any
professional chef would have.

00:15:38,374 --> 00:15:41,310
Now, the stabbing, however,
was less precise.

00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:43,679
I noted tool marks on the ribs.

00:15:43,679 --> 00:15:46,415
(heart beating)

00:15:46,415 --> 00:15:48,618
BRODY: Well, if we can
microsil the tool marks,

00:15:48,618 --> 00:15:51,187
we may be able to
indentify the knife

00:15:51,187 --> 00:15:52,555
and our killer.

00:15:52,555 --> 00:15:55,524
Rod Steward.

00:15:55,524 --> 00:15:58,327
I love his music, but what's
he got to do with this?

00:15:58,327 --> 00:15:59,462
No, that's Rod Stewart.

00:15:59,462 --> 00:16:00,963
This is Rod Steward,
with a "D."

00:16:00,963 --> 00:16:02,698
He's a designer of
high-end men's shoes.

00:16:02,698 --> 00:16:04,300
Very expensive.

00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,901
His size-ten loafer
matches an impression

00:16:05,901 --> 00:16:08,437
on the gel mat that Finn
found at the crime scene.

00:16:08,437 --> 00:16:10,606
Well, that's interesting,
'cause when I was on the set,

00:16:10,606 --> 00:16:13,509
I noticed most of the crew
wearing running shoes.

00:16:13,509 --> 00:16:15,311
So did a lot
of the contestants.

00:16:15,311 --> 00:16:17,413
Well, up-and-coming chefs
don't make a lot of money.

00:16:17,413 --> 00:16:19,215
But celebrity chefs do.

00:16:19,215 --> 00:16:22,318
Graham Deveraux,
our missing judge.

00:16:22,318 --> 00:16:23,919
Not missing anymore.

00:16:35,464 --> 00:16:36,732
(groans)

00:16:36,732 --> 00:16:39,935
You feeling better?

00:16:39,935 --> 00:16:42,338
Oh, just dandy.

00:16:42,338 --> 00:16:44,340
Lot of people have been
looking for you.

00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:45,341
What can I say?

00:16:45,341 --> 00:16:47,243
I'm a popular guy.

00:16:47,243 --> 00:16:49,512
You're also the lead suspect
in a homicide investigation.

00:16:49,512 --> 00:16:51,247
What are you
talking about?

00:16:51,247 --> 00:16:52,615
Derek Barlow,

00:16:52,615 --> 00:16:54,917
the contestant
who attacked you--

00:16:54,917 --> 00:16:56,919
he was murdered last night.

00:16:56,919 --> 00:16:59,388
Oh.

00:16:59,388 --> 00:17:02,892
Barlow is dead. Huh.

00:17:02,892 --> 00:17:04,293
He was stabbed to death

00:17:04,293 --> 00:17:05,461
in the <i>Elite Chef</i> kitchen.

00:17:06,929 --> 00:17:08,931
No.

00:17:08,931 --> 00:17:11,534
Well, that counts me out.

00:17:11,534 --> 00:17:13,602
Judges aren't allowed
in that kitchen.

00:17:13,602 --> 00:17:15,237
It's against the rules.

00:17:15,237 --> 00:17:17,506
If it's against the rules,
then how do you explain

00:17:17,506 --> 00:17:20,376
the fact that we found
an impression of your size ten

00:17:20,376 --> 00:17:23,346
Rod Steward loafer
in the kitchen of <i>Elite Chef</i>

00:17:23,346 --> 00:17:26,749
right next to where
Derek Barlow was murdered?

00:17:26,749 --> 00:17:28,584
(grunting)

00:17:30,853 --> 00:17:32,855
Because I was there,

00:17:32,855 --> 00:17:34,190
but not with Barlow.

00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:35,391
That hot female

00:17:35,391 --> 00:17:37,293
contestant--
what was her name?

00:17:37,293 --> 00:17:39,462
Uh, Cici? Yeah.

00:17:39,462 --> 00:17:42,465
She was showing me
her secret rub recipe.

00:17:42,465 --> 00:17:43,866
What time?
I don't know.

00:17:43,866 --> 00:17:46,469
Around 6:00, after we
finished filming.

00:17:46,469 --> 00:17:48,270
And after
your little hookup,

00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:50,539
you arranged for Derek
to meet you in the kitchen

00:17:50,539 --> 00:17:52,842
so you could teach him
a little lesson.

00:17:52,842 --> 00:17:56,445
Payback for attacking you
on the show.

00:17:56,445 --> 00:17:59,515
Derek Barlow
wasn't just murdered.

00:17:59,515 --> 00:18:04,286
<i>He was carved up, cooked, and</i>
<i>his blood turned into caviar.</i>

00:18:04,286 --> 00:18:06,722
Molecular gastronomy--
which also

00:18:06,722 --> 00:18:08,491
happens to be
your area of expertise.

00:18:08,491 --> 00:18:10,226
Look,

00:18:10,226 --> 00:18:12,695
any idiot can try their hand
at molecular gastronomy

00:18:12,695 --> 00:18:15,364
for the bargain price of $59.99.

00:18:15,364 --> 00:18:17,867
You just buy a kit online.

00:18:17,867 --> 00:18:19,769
Where were you
after 9:00 last night?

00:18:19,769 --> 00:18:21,771
Uh, I was in a limo downtown

00:18:21,771 --> 00:18:24,807
doing body shots of tequila
off two lovely young ladies.

00:18:24,807 --> 00:18:26,842
You can ask them if
you don't believe me.

00:18:26,842 --> 00:18:29,578
Their names were
Candy and Brown Sugar.

00:18:33,449 --> 00:18:35,317
So, you have something for me?

00:18:35,317 --> 00:18:38,354
I found kratom in Derek Barlow's
stomach contents.

00:18:38,354 --> 00:18:40,356
It's a leafy herb
from Thailand.

00:18:40,356 --> 00:18:42,491
Makes the ingestor
irritable and on edge.

00:18:42,491 --> 00:18:44,360
So, Barlow was drugged.

00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:47,196
Might explain why he attacked
Graham Deveraux last night.

00:18:47,196 --> 00:18:49,565
In high doses, that
herb can be fatal.

00:18:49,565 --> 00:18:52,368
So, what if someone
tried to poison him,

00:18:52,368 --> 00:18:53,769
but it didn't work,

00:18:53,769 --> 00:18:56,705
so the killer had
to stab him instead?

00:18:56,705 --> 00:18:58,874
Plausible theory.
Mm-hmm.

00:18:58,874 --> 00:19:02,278
Oh, uh, where are you
and Elisabetta registered?

00:19:02,278 --> 00:19:04,747
I wanted to make sure that
I got you something you need.

00:19:04,747 --> 00:19:06,515
That's very kind of you.

00:19:06,515 --> 00:19:09,485
But, honestly,
I have no idea.

00:19:09,485 --> 00:19:12,254
Elisabetta is in charge
of all things nuptial.

00:19:12,254 --> 00:19:14,390
Really?
All I got to do is get
to the church on time.

00:19:14,390 --> 00:19:15,891
That's funny.

00:19:15,891 --> 00:19:19,361
I always thought of you as
a detail-oriented kind of guy.

00:19:19,361 --> 00:19:20,796
And yet, you're not
even interested

00:19:20,796 --> 00:19:23,365
in planning the most
important day of your life?

00:19:23,365 --> 00:19:25,601
Well, work keeps me very busy.

00:19:25,601 --> 00:19:27,736
Can I give you some advice,

00:19:27,736 --> 00:19:31,240
coming from somebody who's been
down the aisle a couple times?

00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:34,376
You should, um...
you should get involved.

00:19:34,376 --> 00:19:35,644
You should have an opinion.

00:19:35,644 --> 00:19:37,279
You know, band, DJ.

00:19:37,279 --> 00:19:38,914
Roses, lilies.

00:19:38,914 --> 00:19:41,450
I know it may not
seem important,

00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:44,720
but if the groom does not
really care about the wedding,

00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:48,390
it makes the bride feel like
you don't really care about her.

00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:51,193
It's... symbolic.

00:20:03,472 --> 00:20:06,375
Analyzed the tool marks
on Barlow's rib cage.

00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:09,345
Turns out, he was stabbed
by his own knife.

00:20:09,345 --> 00:20:11,380
Guess the, uh, chefs
all have their own

00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:12,581
distinct set of knives.

00:20:12,581 --> 00:20:13,916
They're all kept
in the kitchen.

00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:17,553
Where anyone in the cast
or crew has access.

00:20:17,553 --> 00:20:21,857
Doesn't help us narrow down
our list of suspects at all.

00:20:21,857 --> 00:20:24,293
But this might.

00:20:24,293 --> 00:20:25,961
Curtis LeBlanc,
one of the contestants.

00:20:25,961 --> 00:20:27,830
But according
to that, he used

00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:28,964
to be Curtis Gant.

00:20:28,964 --> 00:20:30,299
It looks like

00:20:30,299 --> 00:20:32,201
Mr. Cordon Bleu has a record.

00:20:32,201 --> 00:20:35,304
Back in 2001,
he served four years

00:20:35,304 --> 00:20:36,705
for possession
with intent to sell.

00:20:36,705 --> 00:20:38,407
Didn't the show
do a background check?

00:20:38,407 --> 00:20:40,843
Well, according to the
producer, just cursory ones.

00:20:40,843 --> 00:20:43,245
Mainly to validate
culinary history.

00:20:43,245 --> 00:20:45,848
But if Curtis lied to the show
about his criminal past,

00:20:45,848 --> 00:20:48,183
that would be cause
for elimination.

00:20:48,183 --> 00:20:50,219
Maybe Barlow found out
about Curtis's secret,

00:20:50,219 --> 00:20:51,587
threatened to expose him.

00:20:51,587 --> 00:20:53,956
Now <i>that</i> would be
motive for murder.

00:20:53,956 --> 00:20:56,692
I perfected my craft in kitchens
all over the world.

00:20:56,692 --> 00:20:58,193
It's my time now.

00:20:58,193 --> 00:21:00,229
No one's gonna stand in my way.

00:21:02,598 --> 00:21:06,235
RUSSELL:
Well, congratulations,
Mr. LeBlanc.

00:21:06,235 --> 00:21:08,537
Word on the street is
you're the odds-on favorite

00:21:08,537 --> 00:21:09,705
to win <i>Elite Chef.</i>

00:21:10,906 --> 00:21:12,408
Not bad for an ex-con

00:21:12,408 --> 00:21:14,410
who honed his culinary skills
making vats

00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:17,279
of mystery meat stew
in the federal pen.

00:21:17,279 --> 00:21:19,515
Of course, you were
Curtis Gant back then.

00:21:22,184 --> 00:21:24,186
Look, I-I was, um...

00:21:24,186 --> 00:21:26,488
I was a new man
when I got out.

00:21:26,488 --> 00:21:29,191
A better man, so...
so I changed my name.

00:21:29,191 --> 00:21:30,859
RUSSELL: But you
didn't tell the show.

00:21:30,859 --> 00:21:33,462
You actually lied
about your criminal past.

00:21:33,462 --> 00:21:35,864
And if they had found out,
you would have been kicked off.

00:21:35,864 --> 00:21:38,667
You would have lost your shot
at a half a million dollars.

00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:41,270
Only one person on the
show knew your secret.

00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,871
That was your buddy,
Derek Barlow.

00:21:42,871 --> 00:21:45,207
As it turns out,
you guys go way back.

00:21:45,207 --> 00:21:48,744
You were frat brothers at
Brassard University in Florida.

00:21:48,744 --> 00:21:50,746
Friends ever since.

00:21:50,746 --> 00:21:52,881
Even roommates
here on the show.

00:21:52,881 --> 00:21:55,484
But, I mean, let's face it.

00:21:55,484 --> 00:21:57,219
Half a million dollars--

00:21:57,219 --> 00:22:01,190
that could turn even the best
of friends into enemies.

00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:02,524
What happened?

00:22:02,524 --> 00:22:04,493
Barlow threatened
to expose your secret?

00:22:04,493 --> 00:22:07,496
Is that why you killed him?

00:22:07,496 --> 00:22:10,766
We know that you tried to
poison him earlier in the day.

00:22:10,766 --> 00:22:13,502
We found trace amounts
of the herb kratom

00:22:13,502 --> 00:22:14,770
in his stomach contents.

00:22:14,770 --> 00:22:16,472
You special-ordered it

00:22:16,472 --> 00:22:19,608
from Thailand two weeks ago,
so give me a break.

00:22:19,608 --> 00:22:21,810
But that didn't kill him,
so you lured him

00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:24,813
into the kitchen
and you stabbed him to death.

00:22:27,783 --> 00:22:29,618
CURTIS:
<i>I didn't kill Derek.</i>

00:22:29,618 --> 00:22:31,654
<i>I wasn't even in</i>
<i>the kitchen last night.</i>

00:22:31,654 --> 00:22:33,789
I didn't stab him and I
wasn't trying to poison him.

00:22:33,789 --> 00:22:35,424
I just...

00:22:35,424 --> 00:22:39,395
I gave him a little kratom
to-to make him sick,

00:22:39,395 --> 00:22:41,530
to throw him
off his game.

00:22:41,530 --> 00:22:44,967
Derek was always
better than me...

00:22:44,967 --> 00:22:46,535
at everything.

00:22:46,535 --> 00:22:48,570
Even on the show, he was
winning every challenge.

00:22:48,570 --> 00:22:51,240
I... just needed an edge.

00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:54,810
So, after you edged out Derek,
where did you go?

00:22:54,810 --> 00:22:56,378
Back to our room.

00:22:56,378 --> 00:22:57,413
How long did you stay there?

00:22:57,413 --> 00:22:58,414
All night.

00:22:58,414 --> 00:23:00,249
Drank till I passed out.

00:23:00,249 --> 00:23:02,484
Look, I-I wasn't trying
to get Derek eliminated.

00:23:02,484 --> 00:23:05,354
I just wanted to win.

00:23:07,823 --> 00:23:09,758
Nice digs
for a reality show.

00:23:11,293 --> 00:23:14,730
So Derek Barlow
was killed in the kitchen

00:23:14,730 --> 00:23:16,699
sometime between
10:00 and 6:00,

00:23:16,699 --> 00:23:18,534
which means Curtis LeBlanc
could have left

00:23:18,534 --> 00:23:20,936
this room anytime
during that window

00:23:20,936 --> 00:23:22,738
and the cameras
wouldn't have picked him up.

