the cup now.

00:35:08,443 --> 00:35:10,578
Maybe he can find out
who tampered with it.

00:35:10,578 --> 00:35:11,813
Let's hope.
Yeah.

00:35:11,813 --> 00:35:13,448
Thanks.
Mmm.

00:35:13,448 --> 00:35:16,418
Hey, um...
do you have a second?

00:35:16,418 --> 00:35:18,553
Of course.

00:35:18,553 --> 00:35:21,289
(sighs)

00:35:21,289 --> 00:35:23,691
Do you...

00:35:23,691 --> 00:35:27,529
think that I'm making a huge
mistake by marrying Elisabetta?

00:35:29,497 --> 00:35:31,266
Uh...

00:35:31,266 --> 00:35:33,635
I can't tell you what to do.

00:35:35,937 --> 00:35:38,440
But I can tell you that,

00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:41,209
whatever you decide,

00:35:41,209 --> 00:35:43,745
I'm gonna be here for you.

00:35:46,748 --> 00:35:48,616
Uh, um...

00:35:48,616 --> 00:35:50,819
I should get back to work.

00:35:57,425 --> 00:35:59,928
So, um...

00:35:59,928 --> 00:36:02,730
I went to this
wedding last year.

00:36:02,730 --> 00:36:05,900
They wrote their own vows,
which was kind of funny.

00:36:05,900 --> 00:36:09,671
But the groom...

00:36:09,671 --> 00:36:12,907
he said something that just...

00:36:12,907 --> 00:36:16,544
man, it stuck with me.

00:36:16,544 --> 00:36:18,546
"Never marry the one

00:36:18,546 --> 00:36:21,316
"that you think
you can live with.

00:36:23,418 --> 00:36:27,322
Marry the one you know
you can't live without."

00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:34,629
SANDERS:
<i>I figured out the source</i>

00:36:34,629 --> 00:36:36,831
of the almond extract
that killed Curtis LeBlanc.

00:36:36,831 --> 00:36:38,399
It wasn't his drink.

00:36:38,399 --> 00:36:39,901
It was his straw.

00:36:39,901 --> 00:36:42,237
<i>Hidden inside was</i>

00:36:42,237 --> 00:36:45,206
<i>a sugar straw laced</i>
<i>with almond extract,</i>

00:36:45,206 --> 00:36:48,776
<i>made precisely to fit</i>
<i>inside Curtis LeBlanc's straw.</i>

00:36:48,776 --> 00:36:51,212
He would have never noticed it.

00:36:51,212 --> 00:36:54,415
So when he took a sip
of the soda,

00:36:54,415 --> 00:36:56,317
it passed
through the sugar straw,

00:36:56,317 --> 00:36:59,320
picking up trace amounts
of almond extract,

00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,855
which then entered
into his system.

00:37:00,855 --> 00:37:02,190
His throat swelled up.

00:37:02,190 --> 00:37:03,591
Good night, Curtis.

00:37:03,591 --> 00:37:05,660
But here's the thing:
when rolling sugar,

00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:07,295
no matter how careful you are,

00:37:07,295 --> 00:37:10,565
<i>it's hard not to leave</i>
<i>an impression.</i>

00:37:10,565 --> 00:37:12,467
Tell me you got a print.

00:37:12,467 --> 00:37:14,569
Better than that,
I got a match.

00:37:14,569 --> 00:37:16,571
Ms. Bradley,
as a producer, I assumed

00:37:16,571 --> 00:37:19,374
you worked your way up the ranks
in television, but...

00:37:19,374 --> 00:37:22,510
as it turns out, you're
a classically trained chef.

00:37:22,510 --> 00:37:25,280
I took courses at the
Culinary Institute of America.

00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,781
Ah, so you learned, uh,

00:37:26,781 --> 00:37:29,918
all about cooking, you know,
from butchering to baking.

00:37:29,918 --> 00:37:32,387
Yeah, I've always been
fascinated with how chefs

00:37:32,387 --> 00:37:34,656
can make almost anything
out of sugar,

00:37:34,656 --> 00:37:37,692
from a sculpture
of a fire-breathing dragon

00:37:37,692 --> 00:37:40,495
to something as simple
as a straw

00:37:40,495 --> 00:37:43,765
laced with
almond extract.

00:37:43,765 --> 00:37:45,633
This is the straw
that killed

00:37:45,633 --> 00:37:47,702
Curtis LeBlanc.

00:37:47,702 --> 00:37:49,871
And that's your print.
We know you
murdered LeBlanc.

00:37:49,871 --> 00:37:52,740
We're pretty sure you
murdered Derek Barlow, too.

00:37:52,740 --> 00:37:55,310
What we didn't know was why
until we started digging

00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:58,212
into your background and
found out that your maiden name

00:37:58,212 --> 00:38:00,214
was Lennon.
Same last name

00:38:00,214 --> 00:38:04,752
as a young girl who was raped
and murdered 15 years ago--

00:38:04,752 --> 00:38:08,222
Sally Lennon,
your little sister.

00:38:08,222 --> 00:38:10,925
And the case
was never solved.

00:38:14,596 --> 00:38:17,398
When they found her, she was
wearing my favorite sweater.

00:38:17,398 --> 00:38:19,434
She was always
taking my stuff.

00:38:19,434 --> 00:38:21,836
It's the only thing
we ever fought about.

00:38:21,836 --> 00:38:23,204
(laughs)

00:38:23,204 --> 00:38:26,174
The case went cold.

00:38:26,174 --> 00:38:27,875
My parents shut down.

00:38:27,875 --> 00:38:31,312
They... they couldn't
even mention her name.

00:38:31,312 --> 00:38:33,348
Must have helped
that your college buddies,

00:38:33,348 --> 00:38:36,184
Derek and Curtis,
were there for you.

00:38:36,184 --> 00:38:37,819
You've been friends
with them ever since.

00:38:37,819 --> 00:38:40,455
When you found out what
they did to your sister,

00:38:40,455 --> 00:38:42,557
you arranged
to get them on the show.

00:38:42,557 --> 00:38:44,926
You wanted them
on your turf so that

00:38:44,926 --> 00:38:46,294
you could kill them.

00:38:46,294 --> 00:38:48,363
No.

00:38:48,363 --> 00:38:50,665
I only found out
three days ago.

00:38:50,665 --> 00:38:54,469
I was going through raw footage,
and saw Michelle coming out

00:38:54,469 --> 00:38:58,239
of Derek and Curtis's room,
half naked, crying.

00:38:58,239 --> 00:39:00,408
She told me about the rape.

00:39:00,408 --> 00:39:03,378
She'd been drugged,
tasted anise.

00:39:04,779 --> 00:39:07,248
Derek's hand was
around her throat.

00:39:07,248 --> 00:39:08,783
Sounded just like

00:39:08,783 --> 00:39:11,386
what happened to Sally.

00:39:11,386 --> 00:39:12,754
So then you confronted Derek.

00:39:12,754 --> 00:39:15,423
Oh...
You and Curtis
raped my sister,

00:39:15,423 --> 00:39:16,824
strangled her, then dumped her

00:39:16,824 --> 00:39:18,893
in the woods like
a piece of trash.

00:39:18,893 --> 00:39:21,262
Nadine, Nadine.
You pretended
to be my friend. You...

00:39:21,262 --> 00:39:23,631
You knew how hard it was for me
all these years.
I know, I know.

00:39:23,631 --> 00:39:25,533
No, no, no. No!
And the whole time,
it was you!

00:39:25,533 --> 00:39:27,735
(grunting)

00:39:29,937 --> 00:39:31,439
(gasps)

00:39:34,342 --> 00:39:37,345
CRAWFORD: I get why
you wanted Derek Barlow dead,

00:39:37,345 --> 00:39:38,746
but you didn't just kill him.

00:39:38,746 --> 00:39:42,417
You carved him up,
you cooked him.

00:39:42,417 --> 00:39:45,553
You served him to people.

00:39:45,553 --> 00:39:49,190
My sister was ripped apart
and eaten by animals.

00:39:51,325 --> 00:39:53,628
My parents couldn't bring
themselves to identify the body,

00:39:53,628 --> 00:39:55,463
so I had to do it.

00:39:55,463 --> 00:39:59,367
I have had that image in my head
every day for 15 years.

00:40:01,302 --> 00:40:04,772
Derek deserved
everything he got.

00:40:04,772 --> 00:40:07,675
And you wanted
to do the same thing to Curtis,

00:40:07,675 --> 00:40:09,744
but there were cops everywhere,

00:40:09,744 --> 00:40:12,914
so you had to make his death
look like an accident.

00:40:12,914 --> 00:40:15,283
I made them pay
for what they did.

00:40:17,351 --> 00:40:20,755
And I finally got
justice for my sister.

00:40:25,293 --> 00:40:26,661
(sniffles)

00:40:33,468 --> 00:40:36,337
Funny thing about Italian ice.

00:40:36,337 --> 00:40:40,808
Some scholars believe that
it wasn't invented in Italy.

00:40:40,808 --> 00:40:43,845
That it was actually
created in China.

00:40:43,845 --> 00:40:45,213
(chuckles)

00:40:47,181 --> 00:40:48,449
David...
Elisabetta...

00:40:48,449 --> 00:40:49,684
Uh...
Uh, sorry.
You go first.

00:40:49,684 --> 00:40:51,419
No, no, you go first.

00:40:51,419 --> 00:40:53,221
(sighs)

00:40:53,221 --> 00:40:55,723
I've been wanting to talk
to you about something.

00:40:55,723 --> 00:40:57,725
And I don't...

00:40:57,725 --> 00:41:00,194
know how to say
this, but, um,

00:41:00,194 --> 00:41:03,197
lately, I... I've
been feeling that...

00:41:03,197 --> 00:41:05,199
David, it's okay.

00:41:05,199 --> 00:41:07,468
I know.

00:41:07,468 --> 00:41:09,937
I've been feeling the same.

00:41:09,937 --> 00:41:14,375
You and I--
we're very different people.

00:41:14,375 --> 00:41:17,745
We both like different things.

00:41:17,745 --> 00:41:21,249
You're not happy here.

00:41:21,249 --> 00:41:23,618
You'll not be happy
in Italy, either.

00:41:23,618 --> 00:41:26,521
You'll miss your friends,

00:41:26,521 --> 00:41:28,923
you'll miss your work.

00:41:28,923 --> 00:41:32,426
(sighs) And if we were truly
meant to be together...

00:41:35,263 --> 00:41:37,732
That wouldn't matter.

00:41:37,732 --> 00:41:40,568
Unfortunately, it does.

00:41:44,605 --> 00:41:47,275
I need to go now.

00:41:47,275 --> 00:41:48,543
(sighs)

00:41:53,648 --> 00:41:55,716
Yeah.

00:42:00,655 --> 00:42:02,790
I will always love you.

00:42:02,790 --> 00:42:04,725
<i>Ti amo.</i>

00:42:15,536 --> 00:42:17,572
Ciao, David.

00:42:17,572 --> 00:42:19,207
I'm sorry.

